This metonymy—easy and natural enough under any circumstances— was particularly likely to suggest itself to the mind of a Latin poet3 for, unlike most civilised nations of modern times, the Romans did not maintuin any standing army; and it was not until the blast of war sounded in their ears, that their soldiers rushed to arms.
